<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1440,1315,1499]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
Snelling (personal communication, 1999) rightly considers Cockerell‚Äôs 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1912" box="[1099,1251,1379,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepeletieri">
<emphasis box="[1099,1251,1379,1403]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. lepeletieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">nomen nudum</emphasis>
because the original description only provided remarks on how specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[1200,1440,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Apis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis">
<emphasis box="[1200,1440,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. haemorrhoidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Hispaniola differ from those of a putative Jamaican species for which he proposed the name 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepeletieri">C. lepeletieri</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
There are no statements describing features of 
<emphasis box="[894,1054,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1912" box="[894,1050,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepeletieri">C. lepeletieri</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
